esh]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Madhesis in Nepal to continue protests till next election, says separatist leader |url=http://www.catchnews.com/world-news/madhesis-in-nepal-to-continue-protests-till-next-election-says-separatist-leader-1454421767.html |accessdate=1 March 2016 |publisher=Catch News |date=3 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306051659/http://www.catchnews.com/world-news/madhesis-in-nepal-to-continue-protests-till-next-election-says-separatist-leader-1454421767.html |archive-date=6 March 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Militant Group: [[Janatantrik Terai Mukti Morcha]], Madhesh Mukti Tigers (MMT), Tharuwan National Liberation Front (TNLF).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.satp.org/satporgtp/countries/nepal/terroristoutfits/mao.html |title=Nepal Terrorist Groups \u2013 Madheshi Armed Outfits |website=satp.org |access-date=30 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915021838/http://www.satp.org/satporgtp/countries/nepal/terroristoutfits/MAO.html |archive-date=15 September 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Terai]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Teraibasi people|Teraibasi]]\n* Proposed state: Terai\n* Political party: [[Terai Army]]\n\n== Pakistan ==\n{{Main|Secession in Pakistan|Separatist movements of Pakistan}}\n{{Further|Insurgency in Balochistan}}\n[[Azad Kashmir]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Kashmiris|Western Kashmiri]]\n* Proposed state: [[File:Jammu-Kashmir-flag.png|22px|border]] [[Azad Kashmir]]<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/19/world/asia/pakistan-kashmir-independence.html</ref>\n* Advocacy group: [[Kashmiri sovereignty movement]], [[Azad Kashmiri Government]]\n \n[[File:Flag of Balochistan.svg|border|22px]] [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Baloch people|Baloch]]\n** Proposed state: [[Balochistan]] [[File:BRA flag.jpg|22px|border]] along with [[Sistan and Baluchestan]] of [[Iran]] and [[Balochistan, Afghanistan|some parts]] of [[Afghanistan]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The Redefined Dimensions of Baloch Nationalist Movement|author=Malik Siraj Akbar|quote=The ultimate goal of BLA is \u201cGreater Balochistan\u201d, a country that will comprise the Baloch areas of Pakistani and Iranian Balochistan provinces and some parts of Afghanistan.|page=29|publisher=Xlibris Corporation|date=30 March 2011}}</ref>\n** Political party: [[Baloch National Movement]], [[Baloch Republican Party]], [[Free Balochistan Movement]] (member of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]])\n** Militant organisations: [[Baloch Liberation Army]], [[Baloch Liberation Front]], [[Baloch Republican Army]]\n\n[[File:Brahuistan.jpg|20x20px]] [[Brahui people|Brahuistan]] \n* Ethnic group: [[Brahui people|Brahui]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Brahuistan.jpg|20x20px]] [[Brahuistan]]\n\n{{main|Sindhi nationalism}}\n[[File:Flag of Sindh.svg|22px|border]] [[Sindh]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bansal |first1=Alok |title=Violent Sindhi nationalism raises its head again |url=http://southasiamonitor.org/detail.php?type=n&nid=2992 |website=South Asia Monitor |accessdate=23 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123092427/http://southasiamonitor.org/detail.php?type=n&nid=2992 |archive-date=23 November 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Now Sindhis Demand Independent Nation In Pakistan|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/world-news-now-sindhi-activists-demand-for-independent-nation-in-pakistan/323750|website=Outlook|access-date=15 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Ethnic group: [[Sindhis|Sindhi]]\n** Proposed state: [[Sindhudesh]] [[File:Flag of Sindhudesh.svg|22px|border]]\n** Political parties: [[Jeay Sindh Qaumi Mahaz]], [[Jeay Sindh Muttahida Mahaz]], [[Sindh United Party]]\n** Student organization: [[Jeay Sindh Students' Federation]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Gilgit Baltistan.svg|22px|border]] [[Gilgit-Baltistan]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Balti people]]\n** Proposed state: [[Balawaristan]] [[File:Flag of Balawaristan.svg|22px|border]]\n** Political party: [[Balawaristan National Front|\nBalawaristan National Front (Hameed group)]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/21-May-2019/raw-network-busted-in-gb?show=preview|title=RAW network busted in GB|date=21 May 2019|work=The Nation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521224017/https://nation.com.pk/21-May-2019/raw-network-busted-in-gb?show=preview|archive-date=21 May 2019|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Gilgit-Baltistan United Movement]]\n\n== Philippines ==\n{{Main|Secession in the Philippines}}\n\n[[Bangsamoro (political entity)|Bangsamoro Region]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Moro people|Moro]]\n** Proposed state: Merger with  {{flag|Malaysia|name=Malaysia}} under the state of {{flag|Sabah|name=Sabah}}\n*** Militant organization: [[Abu Sayyaf]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pike |first1=John |title=Abu Sayyaf Group (ASG) |url=https://fas.org/irp/world/para/asg.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060504010101/https://fas.org/irp/world/para/asg.htm |website=FAS Intelligence Resource Program |accessdate=20 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archivedate=4 May 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Chido |first1=Diane |title=Intel Brief: The Abu Sayyaf model |url=http://www.isn.ethz.ch/Digital-Library/Articles/Detail//?id=91937 |website=International Relations and Security Network |publisher=International Relations and Security Network |accessdate=20 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129022301/http://www.isn.ethz.ch/Digital-Library/Articles/Detail//?id=91937 |archive-date=29 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"pledgebiff\">{{cite news |title=BIFF, Abu Sayyaf pledge allegiance to Islamic State jihadists |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/375074/news/nation/biff-abu-sayyaf-pledge-allegiance-to-islamic-state-jihadists |accessdate=20 February 2015 |work=GMA News |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=16 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128115308/http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/375074/news/nation/biff-a