ation]])\n\n[[Sinjar Mountain|Sinjar]] {{citation needed|date=July 2017}}\n* Ethnoreligious group: [[Yazidi]]\n** Proposed autonomous area: [[Sinjar]] with [[Sinjar Mountain]] region in {{flag|Iraq}} or unification with {{flag|Kurdistan}}\n** Political organisation: [[Yazidi Movement for Reform and Progress]], [[Yazidis]] Community\n\n== Japan ==\n{{Main|Secession in Japan}}\n\n[[File:Flag of Hokkaido Prefecture.svg|22px|border]] [[Hokkaido]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fourwinds10.net/siterun_data/peace_freedom/patriots_and_protesters/news.php?q=1239483589 |title=FULFORD: An Independent Movement Has Started in Japan's Northern Island of Hokkaido >> Four Winds 10 \u2013 Truth Winds |first=Chris |last=Donahue |website=fourwinds10.net |access-date=12 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502031842/http://www.fourwinds10.net/siterun_data/peace_freedom/patriots_and_protesters/news.php?q=1239483589 |archive-date=2 May 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://asiangazette.blogspot.com/2010/02/ainu-claim-independence-to-prime.html |title=Asian Gazette Blog \u270d Jo\u00ebl Legendre-Koizumi: Ainu claim independence to Prime Minister Hatoyama |first=Joel |last=Legendre |date=7 February 2010 |access-date=12 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502005715/http://asiangazette.blogspot.com/2010/02/ainu-claim-independence-to-prime.html |archive-date=2 May 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Ethnic group: [[Ainu people|Ainu]]\n** Proposed state: [[Republic of Ainu]]\n** Advocacy group: {{ill|Ainu Liberation Alliance|lt=Ainu Liberation Alliance|ja|\u30a2\u30a4\u30cc\u89e3\u653e\u540c\u76df}}\n** Political parties: [[Ainu Party]] (\u30a2\u30a4\u30cc\u6c11\u65cf\u515a, Ainu minzoku t\u014d)\n** Political group: [[Ainu independence movement]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Okinawa Prefecture.svg|22px|border]] [[Okinawa]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Ryukyuan people|Ryukyuan]]\n** Proposed state: [[Ryukyu independence movement|Republic of Ryukyu]]<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2013/07/06/world/asia/in-okinawa-talk-of-break-from-japan-turns-serious.html</ref>\n** Political parties: [[Kariyushi Club]] (Formerly, Ryukyu Independence Party, \u7409\u7403\u72ec\u7acb\u515a, Ry\u016bky\u016b Dokuritsut\u014d)\n** Political groups: [[Ryukyu independence movement]]\n** Note: The supporters of the movement want the [[Amami Islands]] in [[Kagoshima Prefecture]], former part of the defunct [[Ryukyu Kingdom]] until [[1609]], to be part of independent Ryukyu. See also [[Invasion of Ryukyu]].\n\n== Laos ==\n{{Main|Secession in Laos}}\n\n[[ChaoFa]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Hmong people|Hmong]]\n** Proposed state: [[Hmong ChaoFa Federated State]] [[File:Hmong Flag.png|22px|border]]\nMember of the [[Unrepresented Nations and Peoples Organization]]\n\n== Lebanon ==\n[[File:ArameanFlag.png|22px|border]] [[Maronites]] {{original research inline|date=February 2020}}\n\n* Ethno-religious group: [[Terms for Syriac Christians#Arameans|Arameans]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:ArameanFlag.png|22px|border]] [[Aram (biblical region)|Aramaean Republic]]\n** Political parties: [[Aramean Democratic Organisation]]\n** Advocacy group: [[World Council of Arameans (Syriacs)]]\n\n== Malaysia ==\n{{Main|Secession in the Malaysia}}\n{{see also | Proposed 2019 amendment to the Constitution of Malaysia | History_of_the_Republic_of_Singapore#Expulsion_from_Malaysia | l2 = Separation of Singapore from Malaysia}}\n\n{{flagdeco|Johor}} [[Johor]]\n*Proposed state: Johor<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.malaysiakini.com/news/344165|title=Bukan TMJ atau PM tentukan Johor keluar Malaysia|date=5 June 2016|publisher=malaysiakini.com|language=Malay}}</ref>\n**Paramilitary organizations: [[Royal Johor Military Force|Askar Timbalan Setia Johor]]\n\n{{flagdeco|Kelantan}} [[Kelantan]]\n*Ethnic group: [[Kelantanese]]\n**Proposed state: Kelantan<ref>http://www.sabahsarawakmerdeka.com/2014/09/kelantan-keluar-malaysia.html</ref>\n\n{{flagdeco|Sarawak}} [[Sarawak]]<ref name=\"ss\">{{cite web |