ryatia}}\n** Political party:All-Buryat Association for the Development of Culture\n\n[[File:Flag of Momsky rayon (Yakutia).png|22px|border]] [[Severo-Evensky District|Evenia]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Evens]]\n** Proposed State: [[File:Flag of Momsky rayon (Yakutia).png|22px|border]] [[Severo-Evensky District|Evenia]]\n\n{{flag|Jewish Autonomous Oblast|}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Ashkenazi Jews]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Jewish Autonomous Oblast}}\n\n[[File:Flag of Nanaysky rayon (Khabarovsk kray).png|22px|border]] [[Nanaisky Raion|Nanaia]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Nanai people|Nanai]] \n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Nanaysky rayon (Khabarovsk kray).png|22px]] [[Nanaisky Raion|Nanaia]] \n*** Advocacy group: [[Nanai Cultural Assembly]]\n*** Political party: [[Nanai People's Platform]]\n\n===Siberian Federal District===\n[[File:Flag of Taymyr Autonomous Okrug.svg|22px|border]] [[Taymyrsky Dolgano-Nenetsky District]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://openrussia.org/notes/717067/|title=\"They keep their dead in the barn\": why they cannot bury the dead in Taymyr|last=Korolkova|first=Elizabeth|date=2017-12-07|website=Open Russia|language=ru|url-status=live|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svoboda.org/a/28638658.html|title=Taymyr residents again demand a referendum on autonomy|last=Starinova|first=Julia|date=2017-07-26|website=Radio Liberty|language=ru|url-status=live|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n* Ethnic groups: [[Dolgans]], [[Nenets people|Nenets]], [[Russians]]\n** Proposed federal subject: {{flag|Taymyr Autonomous Okrug}}\n\n{{flag|Agin-Buryat Autonomous Okrug}} \n* Ethnic group: [[Buryats]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Agin-Buryat Autonomous Okrug}} or unification with {{flag|Buryatia}}\n\n{{flag|Altai Republic}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Altai people]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of the Confederated Republic of Altai.gif|22px|border]] [[Altai Republic|Confederated Republic of Altai]]\n** Movement: Altai-Sayun United Movement\n** Organizations: Altai Turks A