=\"Illinois Song Archives\"/>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n:{{note|id1|a}} The applicable years of graduation from the University of Illinois are listed after a person's name.\n:{{note|id2|b}} While \"Illinois\" is about the State of Illinois, rather than the University of Illinois, it is commonly associated with both.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]\n* [[Marching Illini]]\n* [[Fight song]]\n* [[Alma mater (song)]]\n\n{{University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign campus}}\n\n[[Category:American college songs]]\n[[Category:Institutional songs]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]]\n[[Category:Lists of songs]]\n", "text_old": "This is a '''list of songs written about, dedicated to, or commonly associated with the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]'''. Most of the songs have been composed before 1940, and many were originally submitted in campus songwriting contests.\n\n==Presently popular==\nThe following songs still see regular performance at the university, specifically through the [[Marching Illini]]. Other organizations, such as the Varsity Men's Glee Club, will also perform these songs. They are strongly recognized as university songs.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Composer\n! Lyricist\n! Written\n! {{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Cheer Illini\n| {{sortname|Harold Vater|Hill|nolink=1}} '11{{ref|id1|a}}\n| {{sortname|Howard Ruggles|Green|nolink=1}} '12\n| 1910\n|<ref name=\"Illinois Song Archives\">{{cite web |url=https://archon.library.illinois.edu/index.php?p=collections/controlcard&id=6&q=illinois+songs |title=Illinois Songs and Music, 1903-1958 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=n.d. |website=University of Illinois Archives |publisher=University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign |access-date=March 23, 2020 |quote=Record series 0/1/804}}</ref><ref name=\"University of Illinois Songbook\">{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no b